description:
Under certain circumstances, code assist eats too much code. The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me

baz(x.foo(), x.foo())

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Create a class X with the following code:

```java
public class X {
    void bar(X x) {
        baz(x.foo());
    }

    int foo() {
        return 5;
    }

    void baz(int i, int j) {}
}
```

2. Call the `bar` method passing an instance of X.

Expected Behavior:

The code assist should generate `baz(x.foo(), x.foo())` instead of `baz(x.foo())`.
